      "content": "The debate often centers on whether children should be allowed to change names, pronouns, or gender expressions, with some viewing it as affirming diverse identities and others worrying about developmental readiness. Parents are also divided on whether schools should mandate specific curriculum discussing intersex conditions or hormonal treatments versus education focused on traditional gender roles. Ultimately, the conversation with your child should focus on listening to their feelings while respecting their right to learn things that make them feel safe and included.",
